      "writtenOn": "2026-04-15T21:48:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we just short-circuit instead of introducing `Optional\u003c\u003e` and `map` later on?\nIt would be clearer for the reader and also will exit immediately without going through any additional code.\n\n\n\n```suggestion\n    Account.Id ownerId \u003d revision.getChange().getOwner();\n    List\u003cPatchSetApproval\u003e changeOwnerApprovals \u003d approvalsByAccount.get(ownerId);\n    if (changeOwnerApprovals \u003d\u003d null\n        || changeOwnerApprovals.stream()\n            .anyMatch(isNotCopiedApproval())) {\n      return Set.of();\n    }\n\n    Optional\u003cAccount.Id\u003e maybeAutoApprover \u003d\n```",
