      "lineNbr": 384,
      "author": {
        "id": 1006192
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-04-15T21:48:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The `label` parameter for a change is computed in a single call with `getLabelDefinition(PathOwners owners, ChangeData changeData)`, and it isn\u0027t really a differentiator here because we already know the file names that have been approved by an owner and there is no need to spend CPU time recomping it.\n\nThe only different parameter is the `copied` parameter that is called with `true` and `false` in two conditions. Just provide a specific predicate for it.\n\nThe caller can directly use them in the input set of `PatchSetApproval` and resolve everything in one go, rather than using two different methods with disconnected meaning.\n\n\n\n```suggestion\n  private static Predicate\u003cPatchSetApproval\u003e isNotCopiedApproval() {\n    Predicate\u003cPatchSetApproval\u003e func \u003d PatchSetApproval::copied;\n    return func.negate();\n  }\n```",
